ARISTOTLE.

The Bubo is of the race of Noctuae. and is in aspect very like a Noctua, but not less than an Aquila in size.

PLINV.

The Bubo is a fatal bird, of evil omen beyond other sorts. especially at public auguries; it lives in desert places, and not merely those that are un- peopled, but those also hard of access: monster of the night it utters not a* song, but only a groan. It never flies where it intendS, but is borne off aslant. So Pliny says,

This bird Ι saw at Venice once, of a full Eagle's size¹‚

its legs however, were a little shorter than an Eagle’s legs are wont to be. But it was like an Eagle otherwise.
